    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce driving suspensions for HGV drivers who suffer from a provoked seizure",
        "additional_details": "",
        "background": "The Government should reduce existing requirements for HGV drivers who suffer from a one-off provoked seizure not to drive from five years to three years, and instead require additional annual medical checks once the driver has resumed driving. This could help address shortages of HGV drivers.",
